definition.value: Numerical parameter that quantifies the velocity of a chemical reaction. This parameter encompasses all the contributions to the velocity except the quantity of the reactants.
A fixed and well-defined number or other non-varying mathematical object.
A constant representing the concentration driving force
The role of a solvent in a precipitation or crystallization in which the solute of a solution is sparingly soluble to induce its solidification.
The role of a crystalline solid material input in a crystallization to promote nucleation or crystal growth.

A seed crystal is a small piece of single crystal or polycrystal material from which a large crystal of typically the same material is to be grown in a laboratory. Used to replicate material, the use of seed crystal to promote growth avoids the otherwise slow randomness of natural crystal growth and allows manufacture on a scale suitable for industry [wikipedia].
The role of solids in a slurry
A suspension (AFM_0000442) that is a mix of solids in a liquid
A physical quality indicating  the structural order of a solid in which its atoms or molecules are arranged in a regular, periodic manner.[wikipedia]
A process chemistry datum that quantifies the ratio of the amount of an impurity in the waste stream of a process to that retained in the product stream.
A process chemistry datum quantifying the ratio of the mass of desired compound recovered as crystalline material from a crystallization to mass of compound input into the crystallization.
A debris role of the solution in a slurry resulting from a crystallization
A solid with at least one crystalline phase

A process chemistry datum quantifying the environmental impact of a synthetic reaction, and is computed by the ratio of the total mass of waste generated in the synthetic scheme to the mass of product isolated.
The process excellence index (PEI) is a measure of process reproducibility where the robustness of the procedure is evaluated in terms of yield and cycle time of various operations.

The quality service level (QSL) is a measure of the reproducibility of the quality of the isolated intermediate or final API, and its calculation involves the ratio of satisfactory quality batches to the total number of batches. A reasonable QSL target is 98 to 100 percent.
A planned process with data output of commercial synthetic chemical route.
A process boundary that represents a milestone of filing the documentation required to obtain regulatory approval to sell a new drug product.
A planned process that is about optimizing a synthetic route.
A planned process producing data to demonstrate that a commercial route meets regulatory requirements.
A screening design to evaluate possible chemical reactions
A process that ends with a milestone where a selection will be made on route process.

Chemical kinetics includes investigations of how experimental conditions influence the speed of a chemical reaction and yield information about the reaction's mechanism and transition states, as well as the construction of mathematical models that also can describe the characteristics of a chemical reaction.
A planned process of demonstrating that a process produces product of adequate quality and yield through the definition of the design space or risk assessments.
A screening design to discover polymorphs and solvates of a compound
A process chemistry workflow plan that specifies how a multi-parallel screening study should be conducted.
A planned process of manufacturing one or more batches of a product in unbroken succession. It includes equipment turnover and cleaning can include dry-runs before committing the starting materials.
A plan specification that specifies a process chemistry workflow consisting of a series of unit operations.
An investigation of published material to find prior art related to a synthetic route
A document to secure permission or continuing permission to market a product from a regulatory body.
A planned process about a synthetic route
A planned process of measuring a quality of a material  associated with a process.
A process measurement of the pressure in a process
A process monitoring to determine when a chemical reaction has ended.
A process boundary that represents a milestone of obtaining regulatory approval to sell a new product.
A process boundary that represents a milestone of obtaining regulatory approval to sell a new drug product.
A kinetic determination method to determine the partial order of a reactant by measuring the concentration of that reactant with all other reactants in large excess
A temporal region of initial kinetics of a chemical reaction after which the reaction accelerates.
The assessed reactivity of the mutagenic impurity in the processing conditions

An assessed purge factor based on the solubility of the impurity in the reaction solvent and therefore its propensity to be purged in the mother liquors of steps that involve an isolation of the solid intermediate/product in that step.
A molecular quality that describes the unit cell of the crystal lattice
a symmetry quality of a unit cell in three-dimensional space.
a geometric symmetry that keeps at least one point fixed
a point symmetry that contains a polar axis.
a point symmetry in which the original structure can be obtained by reflecting all lattice points through a single point.
a point symmetry of a structure that is not identical to any inversion of that structure created by reflecting all of its points through a single point.
a non-centrosymmetric point symmetry that cannot be rotated to align with the original structure (chiral).
a non-centrosymmetric point symmetry that can be rotated to align with the original structure (achiral).
the length of the a-axis of a unit cell
the length of the b-axis of a unit cell
the length of the c-axis of a unit cell
